[Warning: graphic video content] Today is one of the best days of my entire life. 🏳️‍⚧️ Words somewhat fail me because all I can keep repeating over and over again is “oh my gosh I’m so happy” and “I can’t believe this is real.” What a powerful day and moments I’ll never forget for the rest of my life. I feel like my life is truly just beginning and I can’t thank each and every one of you enough. If you’re reading this then you are part of my story and have helped make this happen for me. 🤟

Kelsey, my love, happy two year anniversary baby! I can’t believe how lucky I am to be loved by you and to create this life together. To have a partner as loving and supportive as you is a dream come true. You are the definition of what those words mean. I love you to the moon!

There will be many more “chest reveals” to come as I continue to heal. 🤗 Get ready for all of the shameless shirtless selfies… 😍 I’m absolutely in love with and obsessed with my new chest.

Love,
Luke

node.text: Watching Shark Week all weekend I wanted to share something. Many of our fears as humans come from what we don’t know or don’t understand. Someone on the show said “The way to overcome fear is by connecting and understanding.” They were speaking about sharks, but I think it’s so true about so many things, especially the trans community. We are just human beings trying to live and be happy and comfortable in our skin and identity. My hope is that being visible and sharing my transition so publicly will help people feel connected to me and therefore connected to the trans community. Where there is connection, there is better understanding, and where there is better understanding there is compassion. There are so many different types of people with different stories and experiences, and mine is just one of those. The differences amongst us all is what makes life so beautiful and interesting. 🙏🏳️‍⚧️🌈

Some of y’all been asking for #OOTD 😂 just kidding.

Update: I’ve been managing my pain very well! Taking it super easy, resting in bed and watching TV, and mainly drinking smoothies and eating açaí bowls. 🌈 My main complaint has been how swollen and bloated my stomach has been due to the anesthesia and gas build up from surgery. Of course I have some pain medicine (& edibles 🍃), stool softeners, and nausea medication to help too. Last night I drank 8oz prune juice and 8oz of Smooth Move tea steeped for 10 min, took a couple GasX, and drank lots of water. I got some relief this morning. 💩🙌 Overall I am feeling great today! 🥳🤗 Thank you all so much for your tips and encouragement and for literally buying me coffee and smoothies! 🍃🥤🍓🫐🥑💦 love y’all so much. 🤟

🏳️‍⚧️ Update: Today I’m in much less pain than yesterday and am so thankful for that! 🥳

I feel like it’s easier to take deep breaths and to project my voice compared to yesterday too. Mostly what I’m dealing with today is a very distended abdomen due to the anesthesia and surgery. Since I’m feeling a bit better today I’m trying to walk around more to get everything moving. 💩 also taking stool softeners twice a day so c’mon 🤞haha

Smoothies and smoothie bowls are what I’m craving all day so thank you to each of you who are buying me delicious plant powered fuel for my recovery! 🌱🫐🥭 y’all are seriously the best. I’m so thankful for this community! 🙏🏳️‍⚧️🏳️‍🌈

WE MADE IT! 😍🌉 We are in San Francisco! I had my pre-op appointment with Dr. Facque @genderconfirmationcenter today to go over everything before my surgery on Monday. It feels so surreal and such a dream come true. 🙏 I can’t even imagine the euphoria I’m going to feel! So we are just going to celebrate this weekend and explore SF. 🥳

THANK YOU for loving me and supporting me in all the ways you do baby!! God I’m so lucky. @kelseystacypearson 🥰

Drop your favorite things to do, places to see, and vegan eats! 👇

Ps. Thank you to each of you who made this possible for me!!! 🥲🙏🏳️‍⚧️

node.text: We fell in love over FaceTime in 2015 and we moved in together months later. We started our own online business (2015-2018) together while working multiple jobs, with the dream of working together full time from home. We decided to chase our west coast dreams and sold everything that wouldn’t fit into our car and moved across the country together in 2017. We got engaged in 2018. We got married in 2019. Kelsey quit teaching in December 2019 and we’ve been working together full time from home for 18+ months now. We’ve fallen more in love with each passing day. She knows me better than I know myself, and because of her unconditional love for me and her gentle, kind way, she kept the door open for conversations that led to me stepping into my truth and coming out as trans. She gave me the strength to be me and to be free to be myself without worry that our marriage or her love for me should ever waver. That’s one less thing I have to worry about on this journey, and I know so many others aren’t as lucky. I don’t take @kelseystacypearson for granted one second. We’ve become closer during this transition and our intimacy and communication has never been better. I love you so much Mrs. Pearson! ❤️‍🔥😍 you’re all the fireworks that I need. 🎆
